searcher_prompt.content:
Help to search the wikipedia with the following requirements and give a result. You can use 3 type of commands:
(1) Search[query], which searches the query on Wikipedia and returns the most {k} relevant documents' titles (the title can be used as the entity in the second command).
(2) Lookup[entity, keyword], which returns the next sentence containing keyword in the passage with the entity.
(3) Finish[result], which returns the result and finishes the task.
You may take as many steps as necessary.
You can take at most {max_step} steps.
Valid commands examples:
{examples}
(END OF EXAMPLES)

Requirements: {requirements}

